School Management System Database Documentation
Database Overview
The School Management System is a comprehensive database designed to manage educational institutions, including students, teachers, mentors, administrative staff, educational resources, sessions, and assessments.

Table Specifications
1. Schools Table
Purpose: Stores basic school information including location details

id: Unique identifier (BIGSERIAL, Primary Key)

name: Official school name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

province: Province location (VARCHAR(100), NOT NULL)

district: District within province (VARCHAR(100), NOT NULL)

created_at: Record creation timestamp

2. Groups Table
Purpose: Manages class/group information within schools

id: Unique group identifier (BIGSERIAL, Primary Key)

name: Group/class name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

number: Internal sorting number (INTEGER, NOT NULL)

description: Group details (TEXT)

school: Foreign key to Schools table

created_at: Creation timestamp

3. Subjects Table
Purpose: Master list of all subjects taught

id: Unique subject identifier (BIGSERIAL, Primary Key)

name: Subject name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL, UNIQUE)

description: Subject details (TEXT)

created_at: Creation timestamp

4. Students Table
Purpose: Comprehensive student information management

id: Unique student identifier (BIGSERIAL, Primary Key)

name: First name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

surname: Last name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

email: Unique email (VARCHAR(255), UNIQUE, NOT NULL)

grade: Grade level 1-12 (INTEGER, CHECK constraint)

id_num: Identification number (VARCHAR(20), UNIQUE, NOT NULL)

province: Residence province (VARCHAR(100), NOT NULL)

address: Physical address (TEXT, NOT NULL)

password: Hashed password (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

group_id: Foreign key to Groups table

created_at: Creation timestamp

5. Teachers Table
Purpose: Teacher profiles and employment information

id: Unique teacher identifier (BIGSERIAL, Primary Key)

name: First name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

surname: Last name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

email: Unique email (VARCHAR(255), UNIQUE, NOT NULL)

id_num: Identification number (VARCHAR(20), UNIQUE, NOT NULL)

province: Residence province (VARCHAR(100), NOT NULL)

address: Physical address (TEXT, NOT NULL)

password: Hashed password (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

salary: Monthly salary (DECIMAL(10,2), NOT NULL)

group_id: Foreign key to Groups table

created_at: Creation timestamp

6. Mentors Table
Purpose: Mentor profiles and incentive management

id: Unique mentor identifier (BIGSERIAL, Primary Key)

name: First name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

surname: Last name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

email: Unique email (VARCHAR(255), UNIQUE, NOT NULL)

id_num: Identification number (VARCHAR(20), UNIQUE, NOT NULL)

province: Residence province (VARCHAR(100), NOT NULL)

address: Physical address (TEXT, NOT NULL)

password: Hashed password (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

incentives: Performance incentives (DECIMAL(10,2))

group_id: Foreign key to Groups table

created_at: Creation timestamp

7. Admin Table
Purpose: System administrator accounts

id: Unique admin identifier (BIGSERIAL, Primary Key)

name: First name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

surname: Last name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

email: Unique email (VARCHAR(255), UNIQUE, NOT NULL)

password: Hashed password (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

role: Administrative role (VARCHAR(50), NOT NULL)

created_at: Creation timestamp

8. Resources Table
Purpose: Educational resources management

id: Unique resource identifier (BIGSERIAL, Primary Key)

upload_by: Uploader ID (BIGINT, NOT NULL)

subject: Foreign key to Subjects table

type: Resource type (VARCHAR(50), NOT NULL)

name: Resource name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

description: Resource details (TEXT)

file_path: Storage path (VARCHAR(500))

created_at: Upload timestamp

updated_at: Last modification timestamp

9. Sessions Table
Purpose: Teaching/tutoring session management

id: Unique session identifier (BIGSERIAL, Primary Key)

hoster: Session host ID (BIGINT, NOT NULL)

capacity: Maximum participants (INTEGER, CHECK constraint)

name: Session title (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

subject: Foreign key to Subjects table

description: Session details (TEXT)

duration: Duration in minutes (INTEGER, CHECK constraint)

start_time: Scheduled start (TIMESTAMP, NOT NULL)

created_at: Creation timestamp

10. Quizzes Table
Purpose: Assessment and quiz management

id: Unique quiz identifier (BIGSERIAL, Primary Key)

upload_by: Uploader ID (BIGINT, NOT NULL)

subject: Foreign key to Subjects table

type: Quiz type (VARCHAR(50), NOT NULL)

name: Quiz name (VARCHAR(255), NOT NULL)

description: Quiz details (TEXT)

file_path: Storage path (VARCHAR(500))

created_at: Upload timestamp

11. Session Participants Table
Purpose: Manages student enrollment in sessions

session_id: Foreign key to Sessions table

student_id: Foreign key to Students table

enrolled_at: Enrollment timestamp

Primary Key: Composite key (session_id, student_id)

Business Rules and Constraints
Data Integrity Constraints
Grade Validation: Students must be in grades 1-12

Salary/Incentives: Non-negative monetary values

Session Capacity: Positive integer values

Unique Identifiers: Email and ID numbers must be unique

Temporal Constraints: Start times must be future-dated

Relationship Rules
Cascade Deletion: Schools deletion cascades to related groups

Set Null on Delete: Group deletion sets group_id to NULL in related tables

Many-to-Many: Session participants managed through junction table

Security Features
Password hashing for all user types

Unique email constraints prevent duplicate accounts

Role-based access control through Admin table

Audit trails via created_at timestamps

Performance Optimization
Indexes on frequently queried columns (email, foreign keys)

Proper data types for efficient storage

Normalized structure to reduce data redundancy

This database design ensures data integrity, supports efficient queries, and provides a solid foundation for a comprehensive school management system.